_Nathy September 23, 2015 at 2:09 AM UTC

Second one rip
first one meh

as a defender let me give you 2 bits of advice:
1. Don't try and find a defence that will stop 5 ppl at once, you won't find one. If co ordinated well 2 archers can cover 3 rushers comin from multiple angles and you will die. Your primary goal as a defender is to delay opponents for as long as possible so your teammates can arrive. In the rend 3 game in tourney against fort I killed about 3 people. Stormz got about 30 kills from me holding them off and giving stormz time to arrive.

secondly get creative. Anyone can recreate someone else's defence. Most defences i see follow the same kind of style, don't rely on some fancy fences around the monument, just don't let them get near the monument in the first place. Rushers are practicing every day against the usual defences, give them someone new, unorthodox, crazy. Make them second guess or question their approach to the objective. If your defence is something new they've never dealt with, chances are you'll win
